text.tspan: Cost per line of code over time
What you are looking at is the signature of a mess. When systems are thrown together in
a hurry, when the sheer number of programmers is the sole driver of output, and when
little or no thought is given to the cleanliness of the code or the structure of the design,
then you can bank on riding this curve to its ugly end.
shows what this curve looks like to the developers. They started out at nearly
